Package com.ninjaguild.dragoneggdrop.world

Class EndWorldWrapper

java.lang.Object
com.ninjaguild.dragoneggdrop.world.EndWorldWrapper
public class EndWorldWrapper
extends Object
Represents a wrapped World object with World.Environment.THE_END to separate the runnables present in each independent world. Allows for separation of DED respawns.
Author:
Parker Hawke - Choco

    • getWorld

      public org.bukkit.World getWorld()

    • startRespawn

      public boolean startRespawn​(int respawnDelay, DragonTemplate template, DragonLootTable lootTable)
      Commence the Dragon's respawning processes in this world with a specific dragon template and respawn delay. This respawn may or may not fail depending on whether or not a dragon already exists or a respawn is already in progress.
      Parameters:
      respawnDelay - the delay (in seconds) until the dragon spawns (countdown time)
      template - the dragon template to spawn. Must not be null
      lootTable - the loot table to use on death. This overrides any already-set loot table from setLootTableOverride(DragonLootTable). If null, the override will not be set and any existing override will be used (or the template loot table if one was not set prior)
      Returns:
      the result of the respawn. true if successful, false otherwise

    • startRespawn

      public boolean startRespawn​(int respawnDelay, DragonTemplate template)
      Commence the Dragon's respawning processes in this world with a specific dragon template and respawn delay. This respawn may or may not fail depending on whether or not a dragon already exists or a respawn is already in progress.
      Parameters:
      respawnDelay - the delay (in seconds) until the dragon spawns (countdown time)
      template - the dragon template to spawn. If null, a regular dragon will be respawned
      Returns:
      the result of the respawn. true if successful, false otherwise

    • startRespawn

    • setActiveTemplate

      public void setActiveTemplate​(DragonTemplate template, boolean updatePreviousTemplate)
      Set the battle that is active according to DragonEggDrop. This battle instance will be used to generate names and lore for loot respectively. Additionally, the last battle will be set to the current active battle (unless null)
      Parameters:
      template - the battle to set
      updatePreviousTemplate - whether to set the previous template to the current active template (if not null)

      public void setRespawningTemplate​(DragonTemplate respawningTemplate)
